      About this item

      • Comprehensive Health Smart WatchThe activity & fitness trackers watch includes heart rate/blood pressure/oxygen/body temperature/sleep monitor. You can check these real-time health metrics and sleep data(daily, weekly and monthly) conveniently throughout "KeepHealth" APP. You can turn on heart rate tracking for 24 hours, oxygen and temperature tracking at fixed times in the App
      • All-day Activity Tracking and Multiple Sports ModesThis activity & fitness step tracker watch track all-day activity including steps, distance and calories burned to help you achieve your fitness goals more efficiently. It can tracks 25 sports modes such as running, cycling and skipping and more for real-time heart rate, steps, distance, calories burned, time of duration. You could get a map of your workout route and pace in app during outdoor activity by connecting to your phone GPS
      • Real-time Calls and Messages NotificationReceiving a buzzing notification on your wrist for incoming calls, text and app messages including Facebook,Instagram,Twitter,TikTok,WhatsApp,Messenger and more. For incoming calls, you can check the caller name or phone number on the smart watch for men women to decide whether you need to reach out for your phone to answer the call. For text and App messages, you can also read the messages on your watch directly
      • Convenient Life Assistant The multi-functional design of fitness tracker watch for men women provides you with real-time status display, sedentary reminder, drinking water reminder, camera remote, alarm clock weather. The HD color screen comes with three different main screen style options. And 12-hour or 24-hour time format options, C or F temperature options and convenient single-touch control are more user-friendly
      • Customized Watch Face & AMOLED Color ScreenOne-click Controls, make this fitness activity tracker watch more convenient and simple, and high-definition display screen is more fashionable. A variety of dial styles to choose from in the APP, You can also customize the men women smart watch face with photos from your own album

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • Elber
        5.0 out of 5 stars Works amazingly well for the price
        Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2024
        Color: Fitness Activity Tracker Watch--AVerified Purchase
        I bought this for health monitoring during an extended illness. It is surprisingly good at accurately measuring blood pressure. The battery lasts a pretty decent time. I can get by charging it just once a week. The keephealth app is easy to use and has lots of good features.

        There are a few minor issues: the "display" settings supposedly allow you to prevent it from lighting up the display during certain hours, but it lights up anyway, usually because it thinks it detected a "sport" activity, and it's impossible to disable sports altogether. I've been having terrible night sweats due to my illness and so I wake up soaking wet several times each night and have to change clothes/bedding. Whenever I do, the watch always decides I've decided to do exercises and so lights up which is un-helpful in terms of getting back to sleep. It does this in the middle of the night during the time that the display is supposedly set to never light up.

        The sleep detection isn't very good and consistently overestimates the amount of time I'm actually asleep. If you lie still but awake for an hour or two, it will always indicate that you were asleep.

        Blood oxygen, and pulse rate, are pretty much spot-on, the temperature is good in relative terms, but off a bit in absolute terms. That's not a big deal. It's pedometer function is really bad and always way overestimates the number of steps, but I can get that info from the phone directly which is much more accurate so that doesn't matter.

        For the things I want it for, it does a really good job and at a great price, so I highly recommend it. If they could fix the software so it could disable sports mode altogether and actually obey the time limits for keeping the display dark (which would also save battery power because this watch is really bright!) it would be almost perfect as a health monitor.

        Note: I found that wearing the watch so it's face is on the palm-side of the wrist provides good blood pressure readings. There are blood vessels near the surface there; it's not so good if you wear it with the display on the top (back of hand) side of the wrist. This micht explain different peoples experiences.
